The paper describes a system for Inductive Logic Programming (ILP), which is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (AI) that deals with learning from structured data represented in logical form. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The system uses Answer Set Programming (ASP), which is a logic-based programming paradigm that has applications in various areas of computer science, including machine learning and natural language processing. This makes cs.LG and cs.CL also likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses experiments and evaluation, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.SE (Software Engineering).
